---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import PNotes from "../components/PNotes.astro";
import recap from "../img/recap-time-it.jpg";
---

<p-slide class="cover-internal" autoplay>
  <Image
    p-effect="zoom"
    src={recap}
    alt="Recap time!"
    class="alter-image-size"
    style="height: 10em; border-radius: 0.5em;--fragment-duration: 2.5s;"
  />
</p-slide>
<p-slide>
  <ul>
    <li style="margin-block-end: 0.55em;">
      🤝 <span class="main-sub-gradient">MCP</span> — a standard protocol to connect
      LLMs with tools, resources and prompts
    </li>

    <li p-fragment p-effect="from left">
      🖥️ <span class="main-sub-gradient">stdio</span> — local process, zero config,
      ideal for CLI tools and editor plugins
    </li>
    <li p-fragment p-effect="from right">
      🌐 <span class="main-sub-gradient">HTTP</span> — remote service, multiple clients,
      deployable anywhere
    </li>
    <li p-fragment p-effect="from below">
      🔐 <span class="main-sub-gradient">OAuth 2.1</span> — required for public servers,
      use better-auth to avoid reinventing the wheel
    </li>
  </ul>
  <PNotes>
    <p>
      Quick recap of the four pillars of the talk. MCP as the standard, the two
      transports and when to pick each, and OAuth as the auth layer for anything
      exposed to the internet.
    </p>
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>

<p-slide>
  <h3 style="margin-block-end: 0.8em;">
    <span class="cover-internal-sub-section-all">stdio or HTTP?</span>
  </h3>

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5em;">
    <div p-effect="from left">
      <p style="font-size: 0.8em; margin: 0;">⚡</p>
      <h4 class="main-sub-gradient" style="margin-block: 0.3em 0.6em;">
        stdio
      </h4>
      <ul style="font-size: 0.5em;">
        <li>⚡ Local tool or CLI</li>
        <li>⚡ Editor plugin</li>
        <li>⚡ Zero infra needed</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div p-effect="from right">
      <p style="font-size: 0.8em; margin: 0;">🌐</p>
      <h4 class="main-sub-gradient" style="margin-block: 0.3em 0.6em;">HTTP</h4>
      <ul style="font-size: 0.5em;">
        <li>📌 Remote service</li>
        <li>📌 Multiple clients</li>
        <li>📌 Cloud deployable</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p
    p-effect="from below"
    style="text-align: center; margin-block-start: 1em; font-size: 0.6em; opacity: 0.8;"
  >
    when in doubt → <strong>start with stdio</strong>, migrate to HTTP when
    needed
  </p>

  <PNotes>
    <p>
      The decision tree is simple. Start local with stdio — it's the fastest
      path to a working server. Move to HTTP only when you need remote access or
      multiple concurrent clients.
    </p>
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>

<style lang="scss">
  ul {
    li[p-fragment]:not(:last-of-type) {
      margin-block-end: 0.55em;
    }
  }
  div[p-effect~="from"] {
    border: 2px solid #f97316;
    border-radius: 0.5em;
    padding: 1.2em;
  }
</style>
